Ccode\u003Edocker-compose up -d\u003C/code\u003E. Please ensure target data and library folder permission is same with you \u003Ccode\u003Edocker-compose.yml\u003C/code\u003E user.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch2 id=\u0022docker-cli\u0022\u003Edocker-cli\u003C/h2\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EUsing docker command line tool:\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre\u003E\u003Ccode class=\u0022language-bash\u0022\u003Edocker run -d \\\n    --name diosic \\\n    -v \u0026quot;/your/data/folder:/data\u0026quot; \\\n    -v \u0026quot;/your/library/folder:/library\u0026quot; \\\n    -p \u0026quot;3177:3177\u0026quot; \\\n    -e LIB_NAME_1=MyLibrary \\\n    jinker25/diosic:latest\n\u003C/code\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/article\u003E\u003Cscript\u003Ehljs.highlightAll()\u003C/script\u003E","address":"installFromDocker","contentHash":"15f0e2fb3e7354d4a2eb7b7c1c620230150b0b5f15e5539dfbde7dddc7f64330","nextArticle":{"title":"Self Compile","date":"2022-12-26 22:01:36","categories":["Installation"],"address":"installFromCode"}}